article.headline: Texas A&amp,M 87, Prairie View 63
article.story: COLLEGE STATION, Texas -- Khris Middleton scored 18 points to lead Texas A&M to an 87-63 win over Prairie View on Wednesday night. Naji Hibbert added 17 for the Aggies (8-1), which overcame a slow start and held off a second-half rally by the Panthers (2-9). Prairie View leaped to an 8-0 lead before the Aggies scratched back to tie the game 10-10. Texas A&M then built a 36-24 lead at halftime, but Prairie View fought back early in the second period to close the gap to 45-42. The Aggies went on to hit three 3-pointers -- including two by Middleton -- in a little more than two minutes to put away the game. Brandon Webb and Trant Simpson led Prairie View with 11 points each. The Aggies outrebounded Prairie View 46-35.
